{%- comment -%}
  The immersive layer: one fixed canvas host behind all content, the loading
  veil that the intro dissolves, and the static premium fallback backdrop
  used for reduced-motion / failed-WebGL / merchant-disabled visitors.
  app.js decides which of these actually activates — content never depends
  on any of them.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="ts-fallback" aria-hidden="true"></div>
<div id="ts-canvas-root" class="ts-canvas" aria-hidden="true"></div>
<div class="ts-veil" aria-hidden="true"></div>
